Mar 19 2009 	Clean good service great apartment shame there is no restaurant.	I've just returned from a business trip, stayed 5 nights in a lovely 1 bed apartment on the 5th floor, with a fully equipped kitchen, lounge / TV, bedroom / TV, balcony, nice bathroom with separate shower, complimentary fruit and water . Having arrived at the hotel late and up early in the morning I felt very hungry and was very dissapointed to find 'breakfast in the lobby' was literally this - 1 choice of juice, dried croissants and coffee from a machine, right by the reception desk - as you can imagine this was not exactly relaxing. The friendly staff said that the restaurant was under contruction but I couldn't see any evidence of this. So not to be deterred I went for a walk and was pleased to find that Dubai Marina and Jumeirah Beach were about a 10 mins walk and Waitrose/Starbucks in Dubai Marina Mall was across the road, so no real hardship. Having got back from the walk having had a proper breakfast at Paul's patisserie, I decided to go for a relax by the outdoor pool and sunbathe, uh ho - It just didn't quick click that the sun would be hidden by the high rises nearby. So, with a quick taxi ride I spent the afternooon on the beach and enjoyed a refreshing dip in the sea. The evening was spent wandering around and enjoying a really nice indian meal - no artifical colours or flavourings, fantastic!. If you want to be the Jebel Ali end of Dubai, prepared to stay close to a motorway (100 yards) although the double glazing is pretty effective, not have the opportunity for a proper breakfast, swim in the shade at some time of the day and no alcohol then this is a good option. The rooms are superb, beds really comfortable, clean room and the staff are really helpful. A walk around Dubai Marina is a great way to unwind and when the metro is open it's only a short walk to a station so this will improve your independence and choice of transport.	
Nov 4 2008 	great if you want an apartment	I moved to this &quot;hotel&quot; after staying in the nearby sheraton beach resort. Since I was in dubai for 10 days I wanted somewhere that felt like home and the sheraton had a nice view of the beach but the rooms were really noisy from the corridor and rooms above. The radisson is (as the name says) a residential block, so all the &quot;rooms&quot; are more like apartments - studios, one bed and two bed. This was far nicer since I had my own kitchen and even two bathrooms (this was a one bedroom apartment). The apartment was well furnished with high quality bathroom and kitchen and I had a washing machine,full oven/hob and microwave. There was no dishwasher (even though the hotel's website says there should be one) but the cleaning staff would wash the dishes and leave them next to the sink to dry. There was really no noise from the corridor or other rooms and it was really nice to stay there for such a long time.On the downside the hotel is about 5 mins from the beach and like someone else wrote it's really surrounded by a building sites. the good news is that the noise from these does not really get into the apartment and neither does the noise from the nearby 14 lane highway (which you can see in my photos). I would stay there again despite the building work but I would worry that in future years the sites nearby will be built on and your view becomes a face to face view of the apartment block across the road. There is a large shopping mall going up about 100m away (&quot;Amar&quot; in the photos) which I suppose would open sometime in 2009. Apart from that the beach is about 5mins walk away and there is a supermarket and cafes there. about 10mins walk along the marina footpath (which at the moment passes many building sites) is marina walk which has many restaurants and a larger supermarket. The staff were exceptionally poor and not well trained although perhaps they had not been working that long in the hotel business. The porters especially were a bit amateur and they were typically over eager (intrusive) to take my bags even though I could easily cope (I am capable of carrying one supermarket carrier bag up to my room). The hotel's web site is a bit economical with the truth:&gt;&gt;A complimentary shuttle bus will run a regular service between the hotel and the nearby beach as well as the major shopping malls &lt;&lt;this is true but it runs about twice a day, which is hardly convenient. you're better off with a rental car or taxi (although taxi's can take a while to arrive).This should not be a problem once the metro opens (2009?), since there will be metro stations about 5-10mins walk away and from there you can go direct to the city centre, airport and major shopping malls. &gt;&gt;Offering a tempting menu, guests can enjoy light snacks and drinks set in a contemporary interior in our lobby cafe&lt;&lt;the cafe/restaurant is not yet finished (as of Nov 2008), so the website should not tell how tempting the menu is until it opens!&gt;&gt;all studios come equipped with a kitchen complete with dishwasher, washer/dryer,&lt;&lt;&gt;&gt;our spacious Deluxe One Bedroom Residences ... All ... come with amenities found in Standard Studio Residences &lt;&lt;wrong. one bedroom rooms do not have a dishwasher. my first one bedroom room did not have a microwave, but the second one I moved to did. btw beware that ALL studios are on low floors (2-3) so you will have no view and be close to the road. &quot;business&quot; type rooms start on the 12th floor and above (12-20). Overall I loved the room and the view was reasonable (I was on the 10th floor). I would stay there again for sure since I much preferred having an apartment over just a hotel style room. The best points were the quiet rooms, own kitchen (for breakfasts and dinner) and washing machine. A colleague of mine (who was only in dubai for 3 days) did not like it since there was an absence of &quot;normal&quot; hotel facilities like a bar and restaurant. So I suppose it all comes down to what you want.	
Oct 19 2008 	Great apartment but on a ' building site'	Very nice large apartment which was really well kitted out . Luxury bathrooms, well-fitted ultra-modern kitchen, large bedrooms . Whole apartment very clean. This aparthotel has no restaurant, therefore no breakfast was available (except coffe/tea &amp; croissants in the lobby).Downside was the location! Most areas in Dubai are building sites at the moment (&amp; for the next few years I would say) and this was no exception. There were high rise (&amp; I mean high rise!) blocks getting built all around us. The building work goes on 24/7 - but the noise can't be heard from inside the apartment,only from the balcony.Dubai is not a place for children - unless you can afford about £500/night to stay in one of the luxury hotels in the 'completed' locations.Dubai is great for a short visit, there are lots of things to see - but it's not a relaxing 'beach type' holiday.	
